Progress log - recent fixes

1) Fix route -> controller scoping
- Problem: `app/api/accounts/route.ts` passed `session.id` and `app/api/transactions/route.ts` used `params.accountId`, causing controllers to receive incorrect inputs and database queries to be unscoped.
- Fix: `app/api/accounts/route.ts` now passes the full `session` object to `accountController.list/create`. `app/api/transactions/route.ts` POST now parses the validated body and passes `body.accountId` to `transactionController.createUserTransaction`.

2) External transfer support (outside-bank)
- Server: `lib/services/transactionService.ts` ‚Äî added `createExternalTransfer` to atomically decrement account balance and create an append-only transaction record with `metadata.external`.
- Route: `app/api/transactions/external/route.ts` ‚Äî POST endpoint added and validates incoming body.
- Client: `store/services/transactionsApi.ts` ‚Äî added `createExternalTransfer` RTK mutation with optimistic UI patch handling.
- UI: `components/user/transactions/external-transfer-form.tsx` ‚Äî new form component to send money to external banks while keeping existing in-app transfer form unchanged.

Status: done

Notes:
- After these fixes, transactions and accounts are scoped per user/account; please test by logging in as multiple users and verifying each dashboard only shows that user's account and related transactions.
- Next: run the dev server and test registration/login flow; if anything else was reverted, I'll reapply the minimal fixes.

Timestamp: 2026-01-30
 
3) Internal transfer correctness
- Problem: transfers were being created without crediting recipient account and allowed self-transfer, causing cross-user/incorrect ledgers.
- Fix: `lib/services/transactionService.ts` ‚Äî `createUserTransaction` now:
	- verifies sender ownership and account status,
	- prevents transfers to the same account (`CANNOT_TRANSFER_TO_SAME_ACCOUNT`),
	- verifies recipient exists and is active,
	- atomically decrements sender and increments recipient balances inside `prisma.$transaction`,
	- creates append-only transaction records for both sender and recipient with updated `runningBalance`.
- Status: done

4) Admin created-date endpoint
- What: added `POST /api/admin/set-created-date` for admin/superadmin to set `createdAt`/`timestamp` on `user`, `account`, or `transaction`.
- File added: `app/api/admin/set-created-date/route.ts`
- Status: done

5) SSR auth hydration + guard logging
- Problem: on page reload client `auth` slice started unauthenticated and the guard logged `isAuthenticated: false`, causing confusing flicker and prior blank-screen behavior.
- Fixes:
	- `app/layout.tsx`: fetches session server-side via `getSessionFromCookies()` and passes it to the Redux provider.
	- `providers/reduxProviders.tsx`: accepts `initialUser` and dispatches `setInitialAuth(initialUser)` inside a client-side hydrator so the first render reflects the session.
	- `components/auth-guard.tsx`: removed noisy `console.log` and added a timing `console.debug` showing `{ hydrated, isLoading, isAuthenticated, userId }` for clearer tracing.
- Status: done

Timestamp: 2026-01-31

6) Fix login redirect (admin -> admin-panel)
- Problem: `GET /api/auth/me` returned `{ user }` (nested) but client code expects a flat user object. As a result `LoginForm` received `{ user }` and `resolveDashboardByRole(user.role)` saw `undefined` and routed to `/dashboard`.
- Fix: `app/api/auth/me/route.ts` now returns the flat user object (`NextResponse.json(user)`), so login redirect uses the correct `role` and admins are sent to `/admin-panel`.
- Status: done
